        "# Create comprehensive findings document\n",
        "findings_text = f\"\"\"\n╔════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n║                    EXECUTIVE FRAUD DETECTION DASHBOARD - FINAL REPORT                            ║\n║              SAP Procurement Fraud Detection Analytics - Phase 5 Visualizations                   ║\n╚════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\nDASHBOARD CREATION DATE: {pd.Timestamp.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nSECTION 1: EXECUTIVE SUMMARY\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nTotal Transactions Analyzed:           {total_transactions_analyzed:,}\nTotal Fraud Suspects Found:             {fraud_suspects_count:,}\nTotal Financial Exposure (JPY):         ¥{total_financial_exposure_jpy:,.0f}\nOverall Fraud Rate:                     {fraud_rate_pct:.2f}%\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nSECTION 2: FRAUD DETECTION BREAKDOWN\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. DUPLICATE INVOICE DETECTION 🔴 CRITICAL\n   - Suspects Found:                 {len(duplicate_suspects)}\n   - Financial Exposure:             ¥{duplicate_suspects['invoice_amount'].sum():,.0f}\n   - Vendors Impacted:               {duplicate_suspects['vendor_id'].nunique()}\n   - Average Value per Suspect:      ¥{duplicate_suspects['invoice_amount'].mean():,.0f}\n\n2. SPLIT PURCHASE DETECTION 🔴 CRITICAL\n   - Suspects Found:                 {len(split_details)}\n   - Financial Exposure:             ¥{split_details['total_amount'].sum():,.0f}\n   - Vendors Impacted:               {split_details['vendor_id'].nunique()}\n   - Split Purchase Clusters:        {split_details['cluster_id'].nunique()}\n   - Average Value per Suspect:      ¥{split_details['total_amount'].mean():,.0f}\n\n3. ABNORMAL VENDOR DETECTION 🟠 HIGH\n   - Ghost Vendors Identified:       {len(ghost_vendor_candidates)}\n   - Financial Exposure:             ¥{ghost_vendor_candidates['total_invoice_value_jpy'].sum():,.0f}\n   - High Risk Vendors:              {(abnormal_vendor_scorecard['risk_category'] == 'High').sum()}\n   - Medium Risk Vendors:            {(abnormal_vendor_scorecard['risk_category'] == 'Medium').sum()}\n   - Average Risk Score:             {abnormal_vendor_scorecard['vendor_risk_score'].mean():.1f}\n\n4. APPROVAL BYPASS DETECTION 🟠 HIGH\n   - Violations Found:               {len(approval_violations)}\n   - Financial Exposure:             ¥{approval_violations['total_amount'].sum():,.0f}\n   - Departments Impacted:           {approval_violations['approver_department'].nunique(dropna=True)}\n   - Employees Involved:             {approval_violations['approved_by'].nunique(dropna=True)}\n   - Excess Unauthorized Value:      ¥{approval_violations['excess_amount_jpy'].sum():,.0f}\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nSECTION 3: SAP CONTROL RECOMMENDATIONS (PRIORITY ORDER)\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n🔴 PRIORITY 1 - DUPLICATE INVOICE PREVENTION (Transaction: OMRDC)\n   Objective: Activate SAP duplicate invoice check to prevent double payments\n   \n   Configuration Steps:\n   1. Navigate to SAP transaction OMRDC\n   2. Set check scope to Company Code level (all company codes)\n   3. Configure tolerance settings:\n      - Vendor tolerance: 0%\n      - Invoice amount tolerance: 0%\n      - Time window: 365 days\n   4. Apply duplicate check to all vendor account groups\n   5. Activate duplicate invoice blocking for \"Blocked\" status\n   \n   Expected Impact: Prevent ¥{duplicate_suspects['invoice_amount'].sum():,.0f} in exposure\n   Implementation Timeline: Week 1-2\n   \n\n🔴 PRIORITY 2 - SPLIT PURCHASE PREVENTION (Transaction: ME21N / Workflow Builder)\n   Objective: Implement cumulative vendor limits to prevent approval threshold circumvention\n   \n   Configuration Steps:\n   1. Review and reduce individual PO approval thresholds\n   2. Implement daily cumulative vendor spend limits in Workflow Builder\n   3. Configure cross-PO monitoring:\n      - Track same vendor + same day + multiple POs\n      - Set alert threshold at 2+ POs for same vendor on same day\n   4. Create exception report for split purchase clusters\n   5. Block PO creation when daily vendor total exceeds threshold\n   \n   Expected Impact: Prevent ¥{split_details['total_amount'].sum():,.0f} in unauthorized spend\n   Implementation Timeline: Week 3-4\n   \n\n🟠 PRIORITY 3 - VENDOR MASTER HARDENING (Transaction: XK01 / XK02 / OMSG)\n   Objective: Strengthen vendor governance to prevent ghost vendor payments\n   \n   Configuration Steps:\n   1. Activate vendor master change document logging (OMSG)\n   2. Implement dual control for new vendor creation\n   3. Configure mandatory bank account verification:\n      - Vendor registration check\n      - Duplicate bank account detection\n   4. Set auto-block for vendors inactive 12+ months\n   5. Flag new vendors (< 90 days) for enhanced payment monitoring\n   6. Establish vendor approval workflow\n   \n   Expected Impact: Block payments to {len(ghost_vendor_candidates)} ghost vendors\n   Implementation Timeline: Week 5-6\n   \n\n🟠 PRIORITY 4 - APPROVAL WORKFLOW HARDENING (Transaction: SWDD)\n   Objective: Eliminate manual overrides for approval limit violations\n   \n   Configuration Steps:\n   1. Remove all manual override capabilities in release strategy\n   2. Implement hard stop for PO amounts exceeding approver limit\n   3. Add mandatory second approval for:\n      - Amounts within 5% of approver limit\n      - Amounts exceeding approver limit by any amount\n   4. Configure automated alerts for approval violations\n   5. Establish quarterly review of employee authorization limits\n   \n   Expected Impact: Prevent ¥{approval_violations['total_amount'].sum():,.0f} in unauthorized approvals\n   Implementation Timeline: Week 7-8\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nSECTION 4: VISUALIZATION OUTPUTS GENERATED\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n✓ 01_executive_summary_scorecard.html\n  → Interactive KPI scorecard with main fraud metrics\n\n✓ 02_fraud_by_category.html + 02_fraud_category_detailed.png\n  → Fraud category breakdown with count and value analysis\n\n✓ 03_timeline_analysis.html\n  → 12-month fraud pattern trends and seasonal analysis\n\n✓ 04_vendor_risk_map.html + 04_vendor_risk_detailed.png\n  → Interactive vendor risk scatter plot with ghost vendor identification\n\n✓ 05_recommendations_impact.html + 05_recommendations_detailed.png\n  → SAP control recommendations with implementation timeline\n\n✓ 06_master_dashboard.html\n  → Comprehensive master dashboard combining all visualizations\n\n✓ executive_summary.csv\n  → Exportable summary statistics\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nSECTION 5: NEXT STEPS & AUDIT RECOMMENDATIONS\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\n1. IMMEDIATE ACTIONS (Week 1):\n   □ Present dashboard findings to Finance Leadership\n   □ Initiate root cause analysis on {len(duplicate_suspects)} duplicate invoices\n   □ Place holds on suspected duplicate invoice payments\n   □ Identify responsible departments for {len(split_details)} split purchases\n\n2. SHORT-TERM ACTIONS (Weeks 2-4):\n   □ Begin SAP configuration for duplicate invoice prevention (OMRDC)\n   □ Start vendor investigation for {len(ghost_vendor_candidates)} ghost vendor candidates\n   □ Review and document {len(approval_violations)} approval bypasses\n   □ Implement SAP workflow changes for approval hardening\n\n3. MEDIUM-TERM ACTIONS (Weeks 5-8):\n   □ Complete all SAP control configurations\n   □ Conduct user testing and UAT for new controls\n   □ Provide training to procurement and AP teams\n   □ Go-live with new fraud detection controls\n\n4. ONGOING MONITORING:\n   □ Monthly dashboard review and trend analysis\n   □ Quarterly re-benchmarking of fraud detection rules\n   □ Continuous monitoring of ghost vendor candidates\n   □ SAP control effectiveness testing\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nDASHBOARD TECHNICAL DETAILS\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nData Source:                SAP Procurement simulated dataset\nAnalysis Tool:              Python + Pandas + Plotly + Matplotlib\nAnalysis Scope:             {total_transactions_analyzed:,} procurement transactions\nData Freshness:             Real-time analysis as of report generation\nConfidence Level:           Based on deterministic detection rules\nValidation Method:          Fraud flag comparison with hidden ground truth labels\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nCONCLUSION\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\nThis executive dashboard consolidates fraud detection analytics from four specialized detection\nnotebooks (duplicate invoices, split purchases, abnormal vendors, approval bypasses) into a\nsingle, comprehensive visualization layer.\n\nThe total financial exposure of ¥{total_financial_exposure_jpy:,.0f} across {fraud_suspects_count:,} fraud suspects\nrepresents significant risk to the organization. Implementation of the recommended SAP control\nimprovements will substantially reduce procurement fraud risk.\n\nAll visualizations are interactive (HTML format) and can be refreshed monthly as new procurement\ndata becomes available.\n\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\nReport Generated: {pd.Timestamp.now().strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}\nProject: SAP Procurement Fraud Detection Analytics - Phase 5: Executive Fraud Dashboard\nAuthor: Ashek Alahi | MSc ERP Systems (KCGI, Kyoto)\n═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n\"\"\"\n\nprint(findings_text)\n\n# Save to file\nwith open(OUTPUT_DIR / \"FINDINGS_SUMMARY.txt\", \"w\", encoding='utf-8') as f:\n",
